# Initialize medusa-idled if this is an X login session

# Unlike sh, csh doesn't like uninitialized shell variables.
#
# Since this doesn't need to *set* any variables, just to run a program,
# it's easier just to call the sh version than to figure out what's been
# set and what hasn't.

/bin/sh /etc/profile.d/medusa-idled.sh
